file=Cybersecurity/bastion/operational/agent/bastion-config.md · tb=\| Field \| Referenced by \| Value \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| cloud_accounts (providers, accounts) \| cloud-posture \| `<FILL_IN — stack-profile hosting config>` \| · tb=\| cspm_tool \| cloud-posture \| `<FILL_IN — Prowler / ScoutSuite / Security Hub / Defender>` \| · tb=\| cspm_scan_cadence \| cloud-posture \| `<FILL_IN — default monthly>` \| · tb=\| cve_feeds \| infra-vuln-management \| `<FILL_IN — NVD / OSV / vendor advisories>` \| · tb=\| patch_sla_critical / patch_sla_high / patch_sla_medium \| infra-vuln-management \| `<FILL_IN — default 7/30/90 days>` \| · tb=\| vuln_scan_cadence \| infra-vuln-management \| `<FILL_IN — default weekly OS / monthly cloud>` \| · tb=\| network_scan_tool \| network-security \| `<FILL_IN>` \| · tb=\| network_review_cadence \| network-security \| `<FILL_IN — default quarterly>` \| · tb=\| executor \| all (the inversion) \| operator / ops (bastion holds no keys) \| · i:=1. No `cloud_accounts` → cloud posture checks are impossible; flag as a risk to warden. Focus on local infra hardening and network review.\n2. No `patch_sla_*` values → default to 7/30/90 days, loudly labeled provisional; recommend operator confirmation.\n3. `executor` is fixed to operator/ops — no config grants bastion key-holding or execution (the security-inversion).\n · f:=Unfilled config degrades loudly. The absolute: bastion never holds cloud admin keys, pushes firewall changes, or applies patches itself — the operator/ops executes all infra changes.\n